She stands up, her voice taking on a cold, commanding tone that seems to echo even in the small room,  "I’ve tried to reform you, but for all the outward changes, you’re still the same old hateful hunter you always were. Maybe the most use you can be to this world is as a cautionary tale…literally!"

You can feel the wind of her magic whipping up around you, but it's different this time - colder and darker then you've felt before. A chill runs down your spine as you realize this is likely the end for you.

"My what a sad tale, little Red of Ridinghood and the trecherous Blackwolf that consumed her. Of course, I'm taking a little creative license when telling it - I hope you inspire future generations to live better lives than the one you've wasted."

You’re not really sure what she means, but you can already feel the changes starting. Your body is shrinking, reforming into something…else...something not human.

It's nearly instantanious, your body compresses, flattens and folds in on itself a hundred times over. In the briefest of moments, all that's left of you is a small book which tumbles to the floor.

The story of a little girl named Red from Ridinghiod, who went into the woods to meet a nice wytch, but was devoured by the anger of the Blackwolf.

It became quite popular - read the world over. Of course, the title and details have changed over time - you might have even heard a version of the story today.

The End

Ending #2: Storybook Ending

