You do your best to fight, dodge, escape, but in the end, he's bigger and faster. Maybe with help you could have made it, but you stood no chance on your own.

"The Ending" lives up to his name once more, completing his grim mission.

The hunter completes his grim mission.

With his quarry bested, he sets fire to the inside of the cabin to burn away the taint of evil. As the sun sets over the mountains, the first flames begin to flicker through the windows of the small cabin.

It takes a few minutes, but soon the entire structure is engulfed in fire, including the bodies of those inside.

The  solemnly watches. Making sure the fire doesn’t spread to the forest, and that there are no final tricks from the monsters within.

No tricks come, and by morning, there’s nothing left of the cabin but a charred frame and ash.

Life goes on for the residents of Ridinghood, years pass and memories fade. But small towns love their tales of magic and wonder, even though it passes from history to legend, the story isn't forgotten.

Even generations later parents still tell their children the bittersweet stories of scarlet wytches, heroic hunters, and the mysterious little redhead caught between them.

The End

